08/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) have arrested Bosnian Serb Marinko Ljepoja, for suspected crimes against humanity committed in 1992 at Koricanske Stijene in the Vlasic Mountain. 
The 43-year-old man was detained in the town of Prijedor on Monday (September 7th). 
Ljepoja was allegedly a member of a Bosnian Serb unit that killed more than 200 Muslims and Croats in central Bosnia. 
Their bodies were thrown down a deep ravine. 
Twelve other people have been detained in the case so far. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Srna, RTRS, BHRT, Fena, AP - 07/09/09)
